         <p>
                <persName>William Barnard</persName>, a graduate of <placeName>Westminster
               School</placeName> and <placeName>Trinity College, Cambridge</placeName>, was
            consecrated Bishop of <placeName>Derry</placeName> in <date when="1747">1747</date>, a
            role he held until his death. He was one of the few Anglican bishops supportive of the
            Methodist work, as evidenced by his ordination of both <persName>John
               Haughton</persName> and <persName>Thomas Maxfield</persName>. He was married to
               <persName>Anne (née Stone</persName>, d. <date when="1782">1782</date>). See <hi rend="italic">Alumni Catabrigienses</hi>; and <hi rend="italic">ODNB</hi>.</p>
